Practice exercise for sprites and sounds Help Learn more.Discuss

For the last two weeks of class, we will walk you through the construction of the basic infrastructure of a game similar to Bubble Shooter (be patient with the ads). In each step, we will provide a program template and a solution for the step. Many of pieces of code that we will write will be similar to the required code for Spaceship and RiceRocks.

  1. Modify the initial template to draw the firing line used to aim the bubbles. The lower endpint of firing line (the firiing position where bubbles spawn) should remain unchanged. The position of the upper endpoint should move along a circle centered at the lower endpoint and with an angle whose value is contained in the global variable firing_angle.  Use the provided function angle_to_vector to turn the value firing_angle into the position for the upper endpoint of the firing line. Experiment with various value for firing_angle

    2. Firing line template
    Firing line solution

  2. Add key handlers for the left and right arrow keys to the provided program template to control the value of firing_angle and the orientation of the firing line. (We won't use the mouse as in the demo.) These key handlers should work in a manner similar to that of Pong to control the value of firing_angle. Add update code for the firing angle to the draw handler and test whether your code controls the firing line appropriately.

    Firing line control template
    Firing line control solution

  3. Add a Bubble class to the template which has the fields pos (list), vel (list), and color (string). (Note that this class is similar to the Sprite class for Spaceship.) In this step, implement the following methods for this class:

    • __init__ creates a bubble whose initial position is the firing position, whose initial velocity is zero and whose color is generated randomly inside the initializer.
    • update which updates the bubble's position based on its velocity. Include code in this method to cause the bubble to bounce off of the left and right walls.
    • fire which assigns a provided non-zero velocity to the bubble when the bubble is fired.
    • draw which draws the bubble with the given color at its given position.

    Bubble class template
    Bubble class solution

  4. Add code to your program that spawns a_bubble (a global variable) when the programs starts.  Add code to the key handler that fires the bubble when the space bar is pressed.  The bubble's velocity should be parallel to the firing line. Add calls to update and draw in the draw handler to make the bubble move.

    Spawn bubble template
    Spawn bubble solution

  5. Modify the __init__ method for bubbles such that the initializer takes an optional sound. This sound should be played when a bubble is fired. Remember to pass the firing sound to the intiializer when creating a bubble. Test your code with our provided firing sound.

    Bubble sound template
    Bubble sound solution
